{
  "stem": "10768.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And there, we established a hospital also in buildings.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We had an X-ray department.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We had a physiotherapy department.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And all these doctors, somehow nobody was killed, in spite of all the dangers that we went through.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And we were there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But we were not anymore loaded with these very difficult cases, because by that time the other units came closer.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The other units were more equipped.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They had more experienced doctors, specialized in amputations, in head injuries.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were staying in Biesenthal.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And whoever-- whichever soldier we had and all kinds of illnesses, when they got better at that time we were able to send them already back on the Polish territory to Polish hospitals by some kind of way.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We always were taking the directives from the Russian army who was nearby if the terrain is safe, if they can go back.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If we needed some medication, they have helped with medication, with instruments and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But anyhow, the most crucial, heavy, terrible experience was in the city Zaslov-- not Zaslov-- Flatow, which is called Zlotow in Polish, on the same line as Torun and Bydgosczcz.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were going towards-- deep into it to the German territory.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were staying in Biesenthal for [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] probably two months.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The war ended.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At least it ended for the Russian, the German capitulated.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The war still went on on the Japan floor-- Japanese floor-- Japanese front between United States.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But there we knew that Berlin is already taken over by the Russian soldiers.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
